explain basic select t1.c1 as aa, t2.c1 as bb,t1.c2 as aaa, t2.c2 as bbb,t1.c3 as a,t2.c4 as b ,t2.c6 as c , count(*) aaa from t1 inner join t2 on t1.c1 = t2.c1 group by t1.c1,t2.c1,t1.c2,t2.c2,t1.c3,t2.c4,t2.c6;
